     <body>
     <div type="acrostic">
   <pb facs="5"/>
   <lg>
      <l>
         <hi>P</hi>atterne of Learning, Patron of learn'd men,</l>
      <l>
         <hi>E</hi>terniz'd be thy fame by learned Pen;</l>
      <l>
         <hi>T</hi>he
<note n="*" place="margin">For the <hi>Lily</hi> being white, is embleme of purity.</note>
         <hi>Lily</hi> notes thy spotlesse puritie:</l>
      <l>
         <hi>E</hi>mbleme is
<note n="*" place="margin">
            <hi>For</hi>
            <gap reason="foreign">
               <desc>〈 in non-Latin alphabet 〉</desc>
            </gap> the Greeke word for <hi>Pe<g ref="char:EOLhyphen"/>ter,</hi> signifies a Rocke, and is the embleme of Constancy.</note>
         <hi>Peter</hi> of thy constancie;</l>
      <l>
         <hi>R</hi>are are these Patterns for Posteritie.</l>
   </lg>
   <lg>
      <l>
         <hi>L</hi>earne then of <hi>Lilie</hi> (Christians) pure to be,</l>
      <l>
         <hi>I</hi>t is the thing his blest Soule longs to see:</l>
      <l>
         <hi>L</hi>earne of this Saint-like <hi>Peter</hi> constancie,</l>
      <l>
         <hi>Y</hi>e that with him will liue aeternally.</l>
   </lg>
</div>
